      • readAndConvertIFC

        public org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model readAndConvertIFC​(String ifc_file,
                                                         String uriBase)
        public Model readAndConvertIFC(String ifc_file, String uriBase) The method converts an IFC STEP formatted file and returns an Apache Jena RDF memory storage model that contains the generated RDF triples. Apache Jena: https://jena.apache.org/index.html The generated temporsary file is used to reduce the temporary memory need and make it possible to convert larger models.
        Parameters:
        ifc_file - the absolute path (For example: c:\ifcfiles\ifc_file.ifc) for the IFC file
        uriBase - the URL beginning for the elements in the ifcOWL TTL output
        Returns:
        the Jena Model that contains the ifcOWL attribute value (Abox) output.

        private void readInOntologyTTL​(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model model,
                               String ontology_file)
        private void readInOntologyTTL(Model model, String ontology_file) Reads in a Turtle - Terse RDF Triple Language (TTL) formatted ontology file: Turtle - Terse RDF Triple Language: https://www.w3.org/TeamSubmission/turtle/ The extra lines make sure that the files are found if run under Eclipse IDE or as a runnable Java Archive file (JAR). Eclipse: https://www.eclipse.org/
        Parameters:
        model - An Apache Jena model: RDF store run on memory.
        ontology_file - An Apache Jena ontokigy model: RDF store run on memory containing an ontology engine.
